# MiniMem

MiniMem is a local-first long-term memory system for AI agents.

- Local runtime: `SQLite + LanceDB + optional Kuzu graph`
- Runtime-switchable chat/embedding providers
- Memory-cited chat with retrieval traces
- Built for low overhead and fast iteration

Chinese version: `README.zh-CN.md`

## Why MiniMem

- Local-first architecture, easy to run and debug
- Real provider-based chat/embedding/extraction (no mock core path)
- Hybrid memory retrieval (text/vector/graph) with citation traces
- Designed for practical agent memory workflows

## Quick Start

One-click install:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/install.ps1 -RunAfterInstall
```

```bash
bash scripts/install.sh --run
```

Or manual:

```bash
pip install -e .
minimem
```

UI:

- `http://127.0.0.1:20195/ui`

## Configuration

Use env vars directly (or an `.env` loader of your choice):

- Chat provider: `LITE_CHAT_*`
- Embedding provider: `LITE_EMBEDDING_*`
- Graph module: `LITE_GRAPH_*`
- Retrieval profile: `LITE_RETRIEVAL_PROFILE`

Runtime settings can also be changed in UI:

- `Settings` page
- API: `GET/PUT /api/v1/model-config`
- Connectivity test: `POST /api/v1/model-config/test`

## API Overview

- Health: `GET /health`
- Memorize: `POST /api/v1/memories`
- Search: `GET /api/v1/memories/search`
- Chat: `POST /api/v1/chat/simple`
- Graph: `GET /api/v1/graph/search`, `GET /api/v1/graph/neighbors`

